          "id": 15,
          "options": {
            "code": {
              "language": "plaintext",
              "showLineNumbers": false,
              "showMiniMap": false
            },
            "content": "\nOn querying, VictoriaMetrics [tracks](https://docs.victoriametrics.com/victoriametrics/#track-ingested-metrics-usage) how many times the requested metric\n name was fetched from the database (`Requests count`) and when was the last \n time it happened (`Last request`). It helps to identify metric names that \n were **rarely** or **never** queried. \n\n _Note: prefer using [vmui Cardinality Explorer](https://docs.victoriametrics.com/victoriametrics/#cardinality-explorer) over this dashboard for better performance and user experience._\n\n The metric usage tracker is limited by size. \n See panel stats below to see how many entries tracker has, when tracking started and what is its memory utilization.",
            "mode": "markdown"
          },
          "pluginVersion": "12.2.0",
          "title": "",
          "transparent": true,
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "yesoreyeram-infinity-datasource",
            "uid": "$ds"
          },
          "description": "VictoriaMetrics can track statistics of fetched metric names during querying . It tracks only **metric names**, as the number of names is usually limited (thousands) compared to time series (millions or billions).\n\nSee https://docs.victoriametrics.com/victoriametrics/#track-ingested-metrics-usage",
          "fieldConfig": {
            "defaults": {
              "color": {
                "mode": "thresholds"
              },
              "mappings": [],
              "thresholds": {
                "mode": "absolute",
                "steps": [
